    "business_overview": {
        "description": "Reliance Infrastructure Limited, an infrastructure company, generates, transmits, and distributes electrical power to residential, industrial, commercial, and other consumers in India. It operates through three segments: Power; Engineering and Construction (E&C); and Infrastructure. The Power segment engages in the operation of 220 megawatts of combined cycle power plant at Samalkot, 48 megawatts of combined cycle power plant at Mormugao, 9.39 megawatts wind farm at Chitradurga, and 165 megawatts of combined cycle power plant at Kochi, as well as the trading of power. Its E&C segment offers value added services in construction, erection, commissioning, and contracting. The Infrastructure segment is involved in the development, operation, and maintenance of toll roads, metro rail transit system, and airports. The company also engages in the exploration and production of 4 coal bed methane blocks covering an area of 3,266 square kilometers in Madhya Pradesh, Andhra Pradesh, and Rajasthan; and CBM gas block, as well as the rehabilitation and upgradation of NH-66. In addition, it is also involved in the operation of toll road concessions and urban transport systems; operation and maintenance of airports; manufacture of cement and defense systems; electric and electronic products; battery business; telecom and transmission business; and IT business. Reliance Infrastructure Limited was incorporated in 1929 and is based in Mumbai, India.",
